{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "labs::voxelmesh", "icon": "voxel_mesh_alt", "tags": "sidefxlabs,  model, gamedev, voxel, photogrammetry", "version": "2.0", "namespace": "labs"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Labs Voxel Mesh"], "extent": [0, 20]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": [" Convert a Polygon Mesh into a Volume and back into Polygons "], "extent": [155, 224]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["A very common node chain is ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/vdbfrompolygons", "type": "link", "text": ["VDB From Polygons"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vdbfrompolygons"}, ", followed immediately by a  ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/convertvdb", "type": "link", "text": ["Convert VDB"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/convertvdb"}], "extent": [224, 360]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This converts your mesh into a Volume and then back to a Mesh. Doing so has the following benefits: It can close small holes in the mesh, give you new even topology and remove interior geometry. "], "extent": [360, 557]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["VoxelMesh is often used to sanitize photogrammetry data, as it will often fix small imperfections on the mesh. "], "extent": [557, 671]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "text": [" "], "role": "item", "extent": [671, 678], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["UVs are generally destroyed while going through the VDB roundtrip. If you would like to transfer UVs from the original mesh back onto the Voxelized, take a look at the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/labs--uv_transfer", "type": "link", "text": ["UV Transfer Node"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/labs--uv_transfer"}], "extent": [678, 898]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [898, 910], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Resolution"], "extent": [910, 926], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This sets the number of voxels to be generated on the longest axis of the mesh. Note that this is scale independent."], "extent": [926, 1051]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 4, "text": ["VDB Smoothing"], "extent": [1051, 1075], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Dilate/Erode"], "extent": [1075, 1093], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This allows you to expand (dilate) or contract (erode) the geometry along the surface normal of the VDB volume."], "extent": [1093, 1213]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Smoothing Iterations"], "extent": [1213, 1239], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The number of smoothing operations to be applied to the VDB before meshing. This can help remove high frequency details."], "extent": [1239, 1368]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 4, "text": ["Meshing"], "extent": [1368, 1386], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Adaptivity"], "extent": [1386, 1402], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Controls how even the topology of the resulting mesh is. High Adaptivity values mean concentration around areas of high curvature, low curvature means even distribution of polygons\n        ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/voxelmesh_adaptivity.png", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/images/voxelmesh_adaptivity.png"}], "extent": [1402, 1640]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Transfer Surface Attributes"], "extent": [1640, 1673], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This will attempt to transfer any attributes found on the input geometry onto the VDB remeshed geometry."], "extent": [1673, 1786]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Sharpen Features"], "extent": [1786, 1808], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Geometry tends to soften when being voxelized, because some features might sit in between voxels. This strengthens the features and is helpful on hard surfaces.\n        ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/voxelmesh_sharpenfeatures.png", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/images/voxelmesh_sharpenfeatures.png"}], "extent": [1808, 2031]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Edge Tolerance"], "extent": [2031, 2051], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Tolerance for what edges to consider for the Sharpen Features toggle."], "extent": [2051, 2129]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Project to Original"], "extent": [2129, 2154], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Optionally Ray the resulting mesh back onto the original "], "extent": [2154, 2220]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Post Smooth Iterations"], "extent": [2220, 2248], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The Projection step can generate some undesirably overlapping polygons, this step can relax some of those polygons"], "extent": [2248, 2383]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}], "text": "Parameters"}], "title": ["Labs Voxel Mesh"], "summary": [" Convert a Polygon Mesh into a Volume and back into Polygons "]}